abstract: From depictions of a far-left conspiracy to attacks on freshman legislators, the escalating messaging provides a preview of the political advertising to come.
snippet: From depictions of a far-left conspiracy to attacks on freshman legislators, the escalating messaging provides a preview of the political advertising to come.
lead_paragraph: Two minutes after Speaker Nancy Pelosi had announced an official impeachment inquiry, the Trump campaign placed a new ad on Facebook, dropping $12,000 on an “Impeachment Poll” for its supporters.

abstract: The efforts by presidential associates like Rudy Giuliani in Ukraine are helping set up a 2020 disinformation campaign.
snippet: The efforts by presidential associates like Rudy Giuliani in Ukraine are helping set up a 2020 disinformation campaign.
lead_paragraph: Washington is consumed by the impeachment inquiry that has followed the release of the whistle-blower complaint in late September alleging that Trump administration officials and associates sought to coerce Ukraine into politically motivated investigations. Meanwhile, in a parallel effort that appears designed to undermine the integrity of the Mueller report, Attorney General Bill Barr recently traveled to Italy (at least twice) and Britain to gather information as part of his review of the origins of the investigation into Russian meddling in the 2016 election.

headline_main: How Trump Is Helping Russia Help Trump Again

abstract: In first major network sit-down since President Trump’s attacks on his family, Joe Biden called himself the Democratic front-runner and expressed fear that the Trump administration would cause lasting damage.
snippet: In first major network sit-down since President Trump’s attacks on his family, Joe Biden called himself the Democratic front-runner and expressed fear that the Trump administration would cause lasting damage.
lead_paragraph: In a wide-ranging “60 Minutes” interview that aired Sunday, former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. declared himself the Democratic front-runner, defended his son’s foreign business dealings and explained why it was critical for the country’s future to defeat President Trump in 2020.

abstract: Chance also did double duty as the musical guest, and several more surprise guests stopped by the rally.
snippet: Chance also did double duty as the musical guest, and several more surprise guests stopped by the rally.
lead_paragraph: O.K., folks, you know the drill by now: The “Saturday Night Live” opening sketch is a space for the cast and its alumni to run through their various political and celebrity impressions, and this week the setting was a rally for President Trump (played by the increasingly rare Alec Baldwin) held in Albuquerque, N.M. Or, as Baldwin called it, “the great city of Albacore, tuna capital of the United States.”

abstract: One day after President Trump hailed his own record on criminal justice and belittled Barack Obama’s, Democrats hit back at his record and history of racial demagogy.
snippet: One day after President Trump hailed his own record on criminal justice and belittled Barack Obama’s, Democrats hit back at his record and history of racial demagogy.
lead_paragraph: COLUMBIA, S.C. — One day after President Trump claimed he had done more for black voters than the Obama administration had, several Democratic presidential candidates spoke at the same historically black college on Saturday and issued a blistering rebuke of both the president and the event’s organizers — whom they accused of giving Mr. Trump an undeserved platform.

headline_main: Democratic Candidates Rebuke Trump at Criminal Justice Forum
headline_print_headline: Candidates Rebuke Trump At Criminal Justice Forum

abstract: As the House impeachment inquiry enters its second month, there may be no witness investigators want to question more than John R. Bolton, the president’s former national security adviser.
snippet: As the House impeachment inquiry enters its second month, there may be no witness investigators want to question more than John R. Bolton, the president’s former national security adviser.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The message that John R. Bolton, President Trump’s former national security adviser, sent supporters of his newly reopened political action committee last week raised as many questions as it answered in a capital consumed by impeachment.
